$ V11: SOL 101 cantilever torsion — tip torque
$ 1 CBAR element, L=1.0, fixed at node 1, tip torque at node 2
$ Analytical: theta_x = T*L/(G*J) = 4.0*1.0/(1.0*2.0) = 2.0 rad
SOL 101

SUBCASE 1
  TITLE = Cantilever Torsion — Tip Torque
  SPC = 1
  LOAD = 10
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL

BEGIN BULK

$ Nodes
GRID, 1, , 0.0, 0.0, 0.0
GRID, 2, , 1.0, 0.0, 0.0

$ E=2.0, G=1.0, nu=0.0, rho=0.0 (massless; only torsion matters here)
MAT1, 1, 2.0, 1.0, 0.0, 0.0

$ A=0.01 (dummy), I1/I2 small (bending), J=2.0 (torsional constant)
PBAR, 1, 1, 0.01, 0.001, 0.001, 2.0

$ CBAR along X, v-vector in Y
CBAR, 1, 1, 1, 2, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0

$ Fix all 6 DOFs at node 1
SPC1, 1, 123456, 1

$ Tip torque T=4.0 about global x-axis at node 2
$ MOMENT, SID, GID, CID, M, N1, N2, N3
MOMENT, 10, 2, 0, 4.0, 1.0, 0.0, 0.0

ENDDATA
